edu.cnm.deepdive.celestialbodies.units

Class GeocentricCoordinates

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.cnm.deepdive.celestialbodies.units.Vector3
      • edu.cnm.deepdive.celestialbodies.units.GeocentricCoordinates

  • public class GeocentricCoordinates
extends Vector3
    This class corresponds to an object's location in Euclidean space when it is projected onto a unit sphere (with the Earth at the center). This class contains two public methods not commented by the author. This class is made use of by the app Celestial Bodies for the purpose of determining the right ascension and declination toward which the mobile phone is pointing.
    Author:
    Brent Bryan
